name: J%27oopi_Sh%C3%A9
content:
J'oopi Shé was a Force-sensitive Kadas'sa'Nikto male from the planet Kintan who became a Jedi Master in the Technical division of the Jedi Order, the guardians of the Galactic Republic. He was stationed in the Jedi Temple on the planet Coruscant and in 19 BBY attended a briefing given by Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi in one of the building's conference rooms.
The briefing was on the Outer Rim Sieges being conducted by the Republic as part of the ongoing Clone Wars against the Confederacy of Independent Systems. After the meeting concluded, Shé left the conference room while in conversation with Jedi Knight Melik Galerha as Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker rushed past them to enter the room. Shé had blue eyes and scaly gray-green skin. The Nikto wore brown Jedi robes, including brown boots and a brown utility belt where he hung his lightsaber.
J'oopi Shé appeared in the prequel trilogy film Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith, which was released on May 19, 2005. In the current Star Wars canon, he was identified in the 2017 reference book Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia. The name originated in the Star Wars Legends continuity, where it was first used in the deluxe edition of the reference book Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars, which was written by Trisha Biggar and published on October 11, 2005.
